WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.609 --> 00:00:03.308
<v ->March 8th is International Women's Day</v>

2
00:00:03.308 --> 00:00:04.908
and we decided to celebrate it

3
00:00:04.908 --> 00:00:06.464
by talking with one of the founders

4
00:00:06.464 --> 00:00:09.088
of Gather the Women, Marilyn Nyborg.

5
00:00:09.088 --> 00:00:10.881
Marilyn says this group, which is

6
00:00:10.881 --> 00:00:12.939
gathering steam around the world,

7
00:00:12.939 --> 00:00:16.319
does not fit the profile of any other women's organizations

8
00:00:16.319 --> 00:00:18.570
in that they do not have an agenda.

9
00:00:18.570 --> 00:00:20.191
They simply gather together,

10
00:00:20.191 --> 00:00:22.027
uplift and encourage one another

11
00:00:22.027 --> 00:00:24.672
and allow the women's strength to begin showing itself

12
00:00:24.672 --> 00:00:27.798
in the outside world in its own unique way.

13
00:00:27.798 --> 00:00:29.750
Marilyn says, it's time for the story

14
00:00:29.750 --> 00:00:31.839
of a women's value to change,

15
00:00:31.839 --> 00:00:34.367
which can be difficult in an unconscious world

16
00:00:34.367 --> 00:00:37.518
that still equates being feminine, with weakness.

17
00:00:38.208 --> 00:00:40.473 line:15% 
(light happy music)

18
00:00:43.371 --> 00:00:45.663
<v Voiceover>I love this quote, on the website</v>

19
00:00:45.663 --> 00:00:47.574
when you first come onto the website

20
00:00:47.574 --> 00:00:49.940
and it says, "if ever there was a time

21
00:00:49.940 --> 00:00:51.754
"when women shall come together

22
00:00:51.754 --> 00:00:54.281
"purely and simply for the benefit of mankind

23
00:00:54.281 --> 00:00:57.600
"it will be the power of which the world has never known."

24
00:00:57.600 --> 00:01:00.843
And that was by a 19 Century poet named Mathew Arnold.

25
00:01:00.843 --> 00:01:02.762
How appropriate.

26
00:01:02.762 --> 00:01:04.948
<v ->How amazing and what a wise man he was.</v>

27
00:01:04.948 --> 00:01:06.053
<v Voiceover>What a wise man he was.</v>

28
00:01:06.053 --> 00:01:07.367
<v ->Way ahead of his time.</v>

29
00:01:07.367 --> 00:01:08.064
(laughter)

30
00:01:08.064 --> 00:01:09.097
<v Voiceover>Let's get into</v>

31
00:01:09.097 --> 00:01:11.305
how Gather the Women came about.

32
00:01:11.305 --> 00:01:13.363
As I was reading about the history of it

33
00:01:13.363 --> 00:01:15.368
I came across one thing that really struck me

34
00:01:15.368 --> 00:01:17.801
was a little article by Carol Hanson Grey.

35
00:01:17.801 --> 00:01:18.803
<v ->Yes.</v>

36
00:01:18.803 --> 00:01:19.849
<v Voiceover>And I notice that,</v>

37
00:01:19.849 --> 00:01:21.865
I noticed the dates of the inspiration.

38
00:01:21.865 --> 00:01:24.605
it was November of 2001, when women

39
00:01:24.605 --> 00:01:27.113
had started calling her spontaneously

40
00:01:27.113 --> 00:01:30.205
to tell her of their visions that we needed

41
00:01:30.205 --> 00:01:31.805
to gather as women now.

42
00:01:31.805 --> 00:01:32.616
Right?

43
00:01:32.616 --> 00:01:33.628
<v ->Mmmhm, that's exactly right.</v>

44
00:01:33.628 --> 00:01:34.524
<v Voiceover>Right after 9/11.</v>

45
00:01:34.524 --> 00:01:37.004
<v ->Actually, I think, was it after 9/11?</v>

46
00:01:37.004 --> 00:01:38.961
<v Voiceover>I think she said November 2001.</v>

47
00:01:38.961 --> 00:01:40.333
<v ->Oh, I guess you're right, yeah.</v>

48
00:01:40.333 --> 00:01:41.250
<v Voiceover>Which would make sense</v>

49
00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:42.808
'cause that was, a lot of that thought

50
00:01:42.808 --> 00:01:44.468
was going on at that time as I recall.

51
00:01:44.468 --> 00:01:45.345
<v ->Yeah, yeah, yeah.</v>

52
00:01:45.345 --> 00:01:46.592
<v Voiceover>Can you pick it up from there</v>

53
00:01:46.592 --> 00:01:48.010
and explain what's happened?

54
00:01:48.010 --> 00:01:48.714
<v ->Yeah.</v>

55
00:01:48.714 --> 00:01:49.941
Well it's interesting because I called Carol

56
00:01:49.941 --> 00:01:52.640
and after, you know, out of the blue,

57
00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:53.706
someone referred me to her.

58
00:01:53.706 --> 00:01:54.794
And I called her and I said, you know,

59
00:01:54.794 --> 00:01:56.980
I had this idea, it feels to me

60
00:01:56.980 --> 00:01:58.953
like there are so many women's circles

61
00:01:58.953 --> 00:02:01.674
that don't know what the other is doing.

62
00:02:01.674 --> 00:02:05.407
And that using the internet, which she is a genius,

63
00:02:05.407 --> 00:02:07.198
on, on that.

64
00:02:07.198 --> 00:02:11.123
We could be bringing those connections together.

65
00:02:11.123 --> 00:02:13.416
And she said, "Oop, others people are doing that

66
00:02:13.416 --> 00:02:14.856
"but I, we've got a better idea,

67
00:02:14.856 --> 00:02:16.329
"we're going to gather the women."

68
00:02:16.329 --> 00:02:20.500
And I went, "yes, absolutely, I'm on."

69
00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:22.549
And, and there we were.

70
00:02:22.549 --> 00:02:24.834
We gathered, strangers really.

71
00:02:24.834 --> 00:02:27.894
I think 12 or 13 women came together for a weekend

72
00:02:27.894 --> 00:02:29.612
to say what does this really mean?

73
00:02:29.612 --> 00:02:31.146
What does it mean to gather the women?

74
00:02:31.146 --> 00:02:33.418
And why are we doing this?

75
00:02:33.418 --> 00:02:35.370
Well of course a lot of women came up with,

76
00:02:35.370 --> 00:02:36.949
you know, we should be fighting poverty,

77
00:02:36.949 --> 00:02:39.232
and we should be, you know, looking at pollution

78
00:02:39.232 --> 00:02:41.013
and all, all the issues

79
00:02:41.013 --> 00:02:43.871
around war and peace and et cetera, et cetera.

80
00:02:43.871 --> 00:02:45.472
And as we went deeper, we said,

81
00:02:45.472 --> 00:02:47.700
you know there are wonderful organizations

82
00:02:47.700 --> 00:02:50.048
already addressing those issues.

83
00:02:50.048 --> 00:02:53.385
There are very few that are really bringing women together

84
00:02:53.385 --> 00:02:56.062
across all kinds of, of divisions,

85
00:02:56.062 --> 00:02:57.962
to have a deeper conversation.

86
00:02:57.962 --> 00:03:01.034
And to reconnect with the value

87
00:03:01.034 --> 00:03:02.676
of what it is to be a woman.

88
00:03:02.676 --> 00:03:04.607
The feminine qualities within each of us

89
00:03:04.607 --> 00:03:06.793
to go to the deeper nature.

90
00:03:06.793 --> 00:03:09.182
And also that, part of what came out of there

91
00:03:09.182 --> 00:03:11.389
was that all of us were spiritually based

92
00:03:11.389 --> 00:03:12.990
and we wanted that to be the grounding

93
00:03:12.990 --> 00:03:15.399
for Gathering the Women.

94
00:03:15.399 --> 00:03:17.767
<v Voiceover>When you, can you tell</v>

95
00:03:17.767 --> 00:03:22.300
how this has impacted the lives of people globally.

96
00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:23.943
I mea, I mean I noticed you have workshops,

97
00:03:23.943 --> 00:03:26.129
not workshops, but congresses all over the world.

98
00:03:26.129 --> 00:03:27.504
<v ->Mmhmm, yes, we do, we do.</v>

99
00:03:27.504 --> 00:03:28.997
<v Voiceover>And give us a glimpse of</v>

100
00:03:28.997 --> 00:03:32.432
what has happened since this was formed initially,

101
00:03:32.432 --> 00:03:34.438
and how its played out in the world.

102
00:03:34.438 --> 00:03:37.112
<v ->Well let me say what I think is unique about us,</v>

103
00:03:37.112 --> 00:03:40.475
and, and for which some women have criticized us.

104
00:03:40.475 --> 00:03:43.643
We're not issue oriented, we're not saying to you

105
00:03:43.643 --> 00:03:45.840
take a stand on this or that.

106
00:03:45.840 --> 00:03:48.164
We are saying to you, it is important

107
00:03:48.164 --> 00:03:49.882
to get beyond our differences

108
00:03:49.882 --> 00:03:51.931
and to come together as women

109
00:03:51.931 --> 00:03:55.897
for the benefit of all, of all people everywhere.

110
00:03:55.897 --> 00:03:58.640
And so, as my friend locally says,

111
00:03:58.640 --> 00:04:01.221
"when women come together, wonderful things happen."

112
00:04:01.221 --> 00:04:05.818
And that has been our, our basic mission,

113
00:04:05.818 --> 00:04:07.278
is to bring women together.

114
00:04:07.278 --> 00:04:09.338
And, interestingly enough, what we're doing

115
00:04:09.338 --> 00:04:10.968
is very, very feminine.

116
00:04:10.968 --> 00:04:13.870
We are in, inspiring women, we are encouraging women,

117
00:04:13.870 --> 00:04:15.821
we're encouraging them and supporting them

118
00:04:15.821 --> 00:04:18.925
to find their passions, and to take their action

119
00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:20.440
from their own heart.

120
00:04:20.440 --> 00:04:22.574
We don't tell 'em what to do, we often say,

121
00:04:22.574 --> 00:04:25.081
"we connect hearts, we're not trying to change minds."

122
00:04:25.081 --> 00:04:26.477
But we're connecting hearts,

123
00:04:26.477 --> 00:04:28.749
which is desperately needed on the planet right now.

124
00:04:28.749 --> 00:04:31.256
We're such enormous divisions everywhere.

125
00:04:31.256 --> 00:04:34.605
So what we do, then, is we, we invite women

126
00:04:34.605 --> 00:04:37.388
to create gatherings in which women

127
00:04:37.388 --> 00:04:40.247
from all walks of life can come together.

128
00:04:40.247 --> 00:04:43.103
To be inspired, to network,

129
00:04:43.103 --> 00:04:45.238
to hopefully to create circles of women,

130
00:04:45.238 --> 00:04:48.332
ongoing circles of women, so women will be supported

131
00:04:48.332 --> 00:04:50.625
in that effort to find their own empowerment

132
00:04:50.625 --> 00:04:52.938
and their own voice.

133
00:04:52.938 --> 00:04:54.623
Unlike other organizations, again,

134
00:04:54.623 --> 00:04:57.428
we trust the women when they're really excited

135
00:04:57.428 --> 00:04:59.658
and, and in touch with their own passion,

136
00:04:59.658 --> 00:05:00.798
following their own heart,

137
00:05:00.798 --> 00:05:02.751
they will do wonderful things in the world.

138
00:05:02.751 --> 00:05:03.507
Yeah.

139
00:05:03.507 --> 00:05:04.733
<v Voiceover>So really this is an emboldening,</v>

140
00:05:04.733 --> 00:05:08.124
the issues don't, the issues really aren't relevant then

141
00:05:08.124 --> 00:05:11.324
because as you're emboldening women . . .

142
00:05:11.324 --> 00:05:12.327
<v ->Yes.</v>

143
00:05:12.327 --> 00:05:14.481
<v Voiceover>and empowering women,</v>

144
00:05:14.481 --> 00:05:16.295
then they're going to take that forward

145
00:05:16.295 --> 00:05:18.385
in their own unique way.

146
00:05:18.385 --> 00:05:20.315
And start having their voice

147
00:05:20.315 --> 00:05:23.007
in the world of the issues of the day.

148
00:05:23.007 --> 00:05:24.305
<v ->Exactly, exactly.</v>

149
00:05:24.305 --> 00:05:25.574
And you know it's interesting to me,

150
00:05:25.574 --> 00:05:28.763
I think if, if, when a woman is really grounded in

151
00:05:28.763 --> 00:05:30.852
the divine feminine, that, that

152
00:05:30.852 --> 00:05:33.498
piece of self that kinda comes with the package

153
00:05:33.498 --> 00:05:35.472
that has been so incredibly dismissed

154
00:05:35.472 --> 00:05:37.092
over the generations.

155
00:05:37.092 --> 00:05:39.001
When they are in touch with those qualities

156
00:05:39.001 --> 00:05:40.975
and begin to speak from that place,

157
00:05:40.975 --> 00:05:43.221
it doesn't matter if they're speaking

158
00:05:43.221 --> 00:05:46.169
on, on two opposing issues.

159
00:05:46.169 --> 00:05:48.996
They will come to it from a different place,

160
00:05:48.996 --> 00:05:50.266
from a feminine perspective,

161
00:05:50.266 --> 00:05:53.177
which is much more about bringing things together,

162
00:05:53.177 --> 00:05:54.681
much more about compromise,

163
00:05:54.681 --> 00:05:57.465
much more about let's, how do we make it work,

164
00:05:57.465 --> 00:05:59.832
how do we solve these solutions together?

165
00:05:59.832 --> 00:06:02.765
Then, what we see so commonly out there

166
00:06:02.765 --> 00:06:05.273
of division and divisiveness, and,

167
00:06:05.273 --> 00:06:07.683
and the putting down of different opinions.

168
00:06:07.683 --> 00:06:10.104
So, we feel when women are in touch with that,

169
00:06:10.104 --> 00:06:11.769
they will speak from that place.

170
00:06:11.769 --> 00:06:14.724
And again, we trust that that's what will happen with them.

171
00:06:14.724 --> 00:06:17.411
And, I wanna also say that,

172
00:06:17.411 --> 00:06:19.949
I mentioned earlier that, you know,

173
00:06:19.949 --> 00:06:22.947
we know this, that so much or so,

174
00:06:22.947 --> 00:06:27.150
so much of our own feminine selves have been dismissed

175
00:06:27.150 --> 00:06:30.957
by, by the culture, by the patriarch.

176
00:06:30.957 --> 00:06:32.855
And I would say that I think both

177
00:06:32.855 --> 00:06:34.178
men and women are,

178
00:06:34.178 --> 00:06:36.781
had been held prisoner by the patriarch.

179
00:06:36.781 --> 00:06:38.989
Men have been told they can't cry,

180
00:06:38.989 --> 00:06:41.421
they can't have feelings, they can't be sensitive.

181
00:06:41.421 --> 00:06:44.119
And women have been told they have their place.

182
00:06:44.119 --> 00:06:45.953
And that stays in the culture

183
00:06:45.953 --> 00:06:49.228
even though we've had the vote for a little while now.

184
00:06:49.228 --> 00:06:53.001
There is this subtleness in the culture

185
00:06:53.001 --> 00:06:55.649
that, that, that keep women down,

186
00:06:55.649 --> 00:06:58.230
that, that make it very risky sometimes

187
00:06:58.230 --> 00:06:59.393
for women to speak their voice.

188
00:06:59.393 --> 00:07:02.315
Unless they're doing it from a male point of view.

189
00:07:02.315 --> 00:07:03.371
<v Voiceover>Right, which is,</v>

190
00:07:03.371 --> 00:07:05.644
in our congressional leadership for example

191
00:07:05.644 --> 00:07:07.201
and it's, it's very yang.

192
00:07:07.201 --> 00:07:08.919
<v ->Exactly, exactly.</v>

193
00:07:08.919 --> 00:07:10.572
And we're talking about now,

194
00:07:10.572 --> 00:07:12.215
bringing those two things together,

195
00:07:12.215 --> 00:07:14.359
within ourselves, not just the feminine

196
00:07:14.359 --> 00:07:15.862
but masculine feminine

197
00:07:15.862 --> 00:07:18.219
within each of us male and female.

198
00:07:18.219 --> 00:07:21.473
And so, bringing that out into the world,

199
00:07:21.473 --> 00:07:23.767
and coming from that place,

200
00:07:23.767 --> 00:07:26.763
for me it's sort of like the earth is crying

201
00:07:26.763 --> 00:07:27.980
for the voice of the mother.

202
00:07:27.980 --> 00:07:29.164
<v Voiceover>It's crying for balance.</v>

203
00:07:29.164 --> 00:07:30.156
<v ->It's crying for balance.</v>

204
00:07:30.156 --> 00:07:30.764
<v Voiceover>And what we're talking about</v>

205
00:07:30.764 --> 00:07:33.059
is we've had an extremely inbalanced system

206
00:07:33.059 --> 00:07:34.400
for a couple thousand years now.

207
00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:35.840
<v ->Exactly, yeah, yeah.</v>

208
00:07:35.840 --> 00:07:38.133
<v Voiceover>That, I think, I don't think anyone can argue</v>

209
00:07:38.133 --> 00:07:40.127
that point anymore, male or female,

210
00:07:40.127 --> 00:07:41.312
it's way beyond that.

211
00:07:41.312 --> 00:07:42.965
We're out of balance and spiraling,

212
00:07:42.965 --> 00:07:44.543
some would say out of control,

213
00:07:44.543 --> 00:07:45.684
on many many levels.

214
00:07:45.684 --> 00:07:46.494
<v ->Absolutely.</v>

215
00:07:46.494 --> 00:07:47.561
<v Voiceover>Economically, environmentally,</v>

216
00:07:47.561 --> 00:07:49.758
and so balance need to be reintroduced.

217
00:07:49.758 --> 00:07:52.084
And so what you're saying is to find

218
00:07:52.084 --> 00:07:54.014
the harmony and balance between

219
00:07:54.014 --> 00:07:56.424
the masculine and feminine principles,

220
00:07:56.424 --> 00:07:58.078
which really requires extra effort

221
00:07:58.078 --> 00:08:00.467
to get the feminine push back up again.

222
00:08:00.467 --> 00:08:01.438
<v ->You got it.</v>

223
00:08:01.438 --> 00:08:02.558
(laughter)

224
00:08:02.558 --> 00:08:05.341
<v Voiceover>Okay, well and, and in ancient times</v>

225
00:08:05.341 --> 00:08:07.154
in Egyptian times for example,

226
00:08:07.154 --> 00:08:09.266
which is probably the last civilization

227
00:08:09.266 --> 00:08:11.517
we can point to of any advancement,

228
00:08:11.517 --> 00:08:12.775
early Egyptian days.

229
00:08:12.775 --> 00:08:13.746
<v ->Mmhmm, mmhmm.</v>

230
00:08:13.746 --> 00:08:15.590
<v Voiceover>It was very common for the women to rule.</v>

231
00:08:15.590 --> 00:08:17.029
It passed through the blood lines.

232
00:08:17.029 --> 00:08:17.714
<v ->That's right.</v>

233
00:08:17.714 --> 00:08:18.474
(clears throat)

234
00:08:18.474 --> 00:08:19.216
<v Voiceover>Excuse me.</v>

235
00:08:19.216 --> 00:08:22.338
Through the women, and also to be those of the,

236
00:08:22.338 --> 00:08:24.768
that held great importance in the temples.

237
00:08:24.768 --> 00:08:25.587
<v ->Mmhmm, mmhmm.</v>

238
00:08:25.587 --> 00:08:27.771
<v Voiceover>And so now, in what ways</v>

239
00:08:27.771 --> 00:08:30.375
do you see this rising more organically?

240
00:08:30.375 --> 00:08:33.895
<v ->Well it's interesting to me, I, I would, would add to that</v>

241
00:08:33.895 --> 00:08:35.132
since recorded history,

242
00:08:35.132 --> 00:08:37.264
which by the way was recorded by men,

243
00:08:37.264 --> 00:08:38.940
women have been left out.

244
00:08:38.940 --> 00:08:41.404
And so I guess you might say many women

245
00:08:41.404 --> 00:08:42.652
have taken that personally

246
00:08:42.652 --> 00:08:45.670
and have acted under, under sort of, you know,

247
00:08:45.670 --> 00:08:47.386
beneath the surface if you will.

248
00:08:47.386 --> 00:08:48.389
<v Voiceover>More manipulatively</v>

249
00:08:48.389 --> 00:08:49.669
because it couldn't be done in the open.

250
00:08:49.669 --> 00:08:51.311
<v ->Yes, yes, that's correct, that's correct.</v>

251
00:08:51.311 --> 00:08:52.805
And, and what we're really calling for

252
00:08:52.805 --> 00:08:55.129
is the voice of, first of all for women, to,

253
00:08:55.129 --> 00:08:57.519
to discover their passions, to find their voice

254
00:08:57.519 --> 00:08:58.980
and to bring it into the world

255
00:08:58.980 --> 00:09:00.377
wherever they may be.

256
00:09:00.377 --> 00:09:02.468
In their homes, in their communities,

257
00:09:02.468 --> 00:09:04.345
and certainly in the world itself.

258
00:09:04.345 --> 00:09:07.385
And that is, that message rings true

259
00:09:07.385 --> 00:09:09.753
for women around the world.

260
00:09:09.753 --> 00:09:12.238
For me personally, I've had the experience

